'''Denise W. Merrill'''  is a [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] politician and the current [[Secretary of the State of Connecticut|Connecticut Secretary of the State]].<ref>http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/files/elections/2010/general/by_state/statewide/CT.html?SITE=CTHARELN&SECTION=POLITICS</ref> Merrill was previously a member of the [[Connecticut House of Representatives]].

==Education== 

Merrill graduated from the [[University of Connecticut]].<ref>http://www.sots.ct.gov/sots/cwp/view.asp?a=3181&q=469626</ref> 

==State House==

Merrill was first elected to office in 1994 and served as the House [[Majority Leader]] after being elected to that position prior to the 2009 legislative session and until becoming Secretary of the State. Previously, Merrill had served as the House Chair on the Appropriations Committee from 2005-2008. In the State House she represented [[Connecticut's 54th assembly district|Fifty-Fourth Assembly District]], which includes the towns of [[Mansfield, Connecticut|Mansfield]] and [[Chaplin, Connecticut|Chaplin]].

==Secretary of State==

Following the state Democratic primary held on August 10, 2010, Merrill became her party's nominee for Secretary of the State for the November 2010 election.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://blogs.courant.com/capitol_watch/2010/08/connecticut-primaries-state-ho.html |title=Connecticut Primaries: Results|publisher=''[[Hartford Courant]]''|date=August 10, 2010|accessdate=August 12, 2010}}</ref> She went on to defeat Republican candidate [[Jerry Farrell Jr.]] on November 2.

==Personal==

Merrill is also a classically trained pianist. She has three grown children and one grandchild.<ref>http://www.sots.ct.gov/sots/cwp/view.asp?a=3181&q=469626</ref> 


